+When recent failed manifests include Python `SyntaxError`, `py_compile`, or TypeScript `TS1005`/`TS1109`/`TS1128`, do not ask the worker to retry a broad contract rewrite. Move to a smaller recovery path:
 
-- Return a smaller proposal than the failed attempt.
-- Prefer one implementation file plus one focused test file and, only when necessary, one or two tiny fixtures.
-- Avoid broad contract rewrites, multi-module refactors, or task-board status edits.
